DISCIPLINARY DOCKET

99-372. Cincinnati Bar Assn. v. Harwood.

This matter came on for further consideration upon the filing on July 25, 2000, by respondent, David J. Harwood, of a motion to set aside finding of contempt. Upon consideration thereof,

IT IS ORDERED by this court that the motion be, and hereby is, granted, and that respondent is purged of contempt in this matter.
